Nokia has lodged objections to the Lokia brand application to the Industrial Property Office. According to CCV, however, product confusion is not likely.
A Brno firm developing CCV software is facing legal action from Finnish telecoms equipment maker Nokia. Finns don't like the fact that a Brno warehouse management firm's program is called Lokia WMS, the newspaper E15 wrote. Nokia has therefore lodged objections to the Lokia brand application to the Industrial Property Office. CCV judges that confusion is not likely.
Marketing director Petr Ondrášek said that the program is already used by two dozen customers, the market has been on since last September.
