The administration of the Krkonoše National Park (KRNAP) by three weeks pushed the bidding deadline to the second tender for the repair of the Krkonoše Museum in Vrchlabi. The original opening date for envelopes was September 20, Radek Dear National Park spokesman said. The reason for shifting the deadline for submitting bids is to reduce the budget from 110 million kronor to 83 million kronor.
“We are currently working with prices that are on the market. There's been a change in the budget, it's about the price we expect to be offered. If someone makes an offer that is acceptable, then the works will begin as much as possible,” Dear said.
Opposite the original plans, the museum's repair start is about a year late. KRNAP wanted to have a selected construction part contractor by the end of last year and start construction work this spring. According to the management of the National Park Administration, European subsidies of 123 million crowns for the project are not at risk.
The administration of KRNAP is failing to choose the construction company to repair the museum. It listed the second competition this summer because, in the previous tender, all of the firms” offerings significantly exceeded the then-projected price of 65 million. Offers exceeded 100 million kroner.
