Costa Rica can boast almost 30 national parks, which, given the country's not-large expanse (51,100 square kilometers), is really a lot. Rainfall or misty forests, coral reefs or mangrove marshes are home to five percent of the world's biodiversity. The country also has volcanoes, pitoreque waterfalls, and you would also find several salvage stations for sloths.
