Annex 12/Safety rules
1. Definition of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following expressions and verbal connections have the following meaning:
A security incident implies any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information Asset means any information, processes, hardware or software components that (1) support the business activities of the Authorized Entity or (2) have for the Authorised Entity value, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorised change or unavailability has a negative impact on the Authorised Entity.
The person of the Contractor means persons directly or indirectly involved in the performance of the subject of this Agreement, including the persons subcontractors of the Contractor.
The environment of the Authorised Entity means the premises in which the Authorised Entity carries out its business activities and the information-communication systems used by the Authorised Entity and which contain Information Assets.
2. Personnel safety
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 does not have a criminal record;
2.1.2 has not been convicted of a deliberate offence in the past and is not criminally prosecuted at the time of fulfilment of the subject of this Treaty,
2.2 If the Contractor finds inconsistency with the abovementioned rules, he must inform the Orderer without delay. The Orderer is entitled to require that such person should not further participate in the implementation of the works resulting from the subject of this Agreement, directly or indirectly, and is entitled to request the Contractor ensuring adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Orderer with a complete name list of the Contractor's Persons. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Orderer of changes in the personnel security performance of this Agreement in advance.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 shall be acquainted with these safety rules,
2.4.2 shall have all necessary tests and attestations resulting from the law or requirements of the Regulator for the type of work to be carried out in connection with the implementation of this Treaty;
2.4.3 are the Contractor of regular training in the fields of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Persons shall not enter the Environment under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, combustibles, fighting means, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substances threatening human life and/or health.
3. Physical safety
3.1 Access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of an Authorised Body shall be permitted only if their presence is necessary for the fulfilment of the employment obligations under this Agreement.
3.2 The Contractor's persons always move in the Environment of the Authorized Entity accompanied by the Responsible Officer of the Orderer.
3.3 The free movement of Contractor's Persons in the Authorised Entity Environment is permitted only if the person has been issued a personal access card. The Contractor may not further lend the Access Card to third parties or allow third party access to the Authorised Entity Environment.
3.4 In case of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to inform the Orderer without delay.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of work resulting from this Agreement or after the termination of this Agreement, or if there is no longer further physical access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of the Authorized the entity needed, the Orderer shall ensure that all Contractor's Persons return the loaned access cards to the Orderer.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Orderer, the Contractor person may not take away any Information assets from the Environment of the Authorized Entity via the storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of Contractor's Persons in the Authorised Entity Environment
4.1 The Contractor's Persons are assigned only accounts allowing unambiguous identification of the User and only with the authorisations they need to carry out their work duties resulting from this Treaty.
4.2 Common work acts are carried out by the Contractor under unprivileged accounts, accounts with administrator privileges are used only when necessary.
4.3 Contractor persons may not access the Internet if they operate under an account with administrator privileges or applications that are running under administrator privileges.
4.4 The contractor's inactive accounts are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Customer.
4.5 Shared Accounts is used by the Contractor only with the prior written consent of the Orderer.
4.6 In case of a password disclosure or in case of suspicion of discarding a password, the Contractor must immediately arrange a change or block of the password.
5. Dealing with certificates
5.1 Access to certificates (both logical and physical) will be allowed only to those Contractor persons for whom such access is necessary for the fulfilment of their duties.
5.2 Without the written consent of the Contractor's Person, the certificates may not be provided or made available to third parties.
5.3 After they are installed, the certificates can only be stored in secure storage in places where they are stored is necessary for the fulfilment of this Agreement and will destroy any other copies in a manner, which makes it impossible to re-restore them.
5.4 If possible, the private certificate key must be set as non-exportable. The private certificate key must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in an unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to inform the Orderer without delay of loss or suspicion of loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Management of Information Assets
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited only to locations that exclude the unauthorised disclosure of sensitive information. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in mass transit, public places and places where industrial cameras are imminent.
6.2 After the completion of the works resulting from this Agreement, the Contractor shall return or remove all Information assets deposited in the Contractor's environment without undue delay, if the possession of these information is not required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be done in a way that makes it impossible to re-restore them.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not grant access to Information Assets to any third parties not authorized to participate in the performance of this Agreement.
6.4 The contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which information assets are stored, processed or through which are transmitted. In connection with Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders or files so as to exclude unauthorized access to Information Assets,
6.4.2, malicious code detection and removal tools are used with the setting of a regular update of the malicious code signature database with a frequency not exceeding one week and are appropriate surveillance, logging and response processes to a positive detection of malicious code are set,
6.4.3 are defined, set, performed and monitored by updating software component security patches in an interval not exceeding one month from the release of patches;
6.4.4, the Internet environment is separated by a firewall that is connected to surveillance and Contractor Persons use exclusively an encrypted VPN connection to prevent unauthorized interception and change of transmitted communication.
6.5 Where Information Assets are transmitted by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorised Body, the Contractor shall be obliged to ensure the physical security of these assets and have such Information Assets still under surveillance. The contractor is obliged to follow the security and operational instructions of the hardware manufacturer on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Work in Authorized Entity Environment
7.1 The contractor is obliged to familiarize himself and act in accordance with the Information Assets Classification Standard if the Orderer provides it to him.
7.2 For hardware that is owned and managed by the Orderer or hardware, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Orderer, the Contractor may not perform by the Orderer unapproved configuration changes for this hardware. In particular, the contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware so installed, the process of applying security patches must be explicitly and formally established, including responsibilities arising from roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Customer, the Contractor may not install or run any pre-approved software by the Customer.
7.4 Without the written consent of the Customer, the Contractor shall not be authorised to conduct any physical or logical safety testing or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorised Body .
7.5 The contractor shall not manipulate audit records in any way.
7.6 Contractor persons are not authorised to work with software, hardware or data content which is not directly related to the implementation of this Agreement.
7.7 Contractor persons may not carry out any activities prejudicial to other natural or legal persons, including sending out unsolicited emails, sending out fraudulent emails, distribution malicious code or participating in attacks in order to disable the availability of services.
7.8 All steps carried out by the Contractor's Persons, the Orderer logs and keeps the record of them for 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Procurer, the Contractor's Persons may not connect their own storage devices to any device of the Authorised Entity's computer technology.
7.10 In the place provided, the Contractor's persons shall, after the time of physical absence, ensure:
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the work place can be safely used;
7.10.2 Adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logically locking access to Information Assets so that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 The Contractor's persons are not authorised to install devices allowing remote interception or to make any audio or video recording without the prior written consent of the Orderer.
8. Crisis management
8.1 Contractor persons are obliged to prevent, to the highest possible extent, the emergence of crisis situations (e.g. fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury may occur or damage to the property of the authorized person.
8.2 In case of emergence of a crisis situation, the Contractor's person who is physically present at the site of the event is obliged without exception and delay to comply with the regulations and directives in force in the locality; and obey instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercise.
8.3 In case of emergency management, the Contractor's Person is obliged to obey the instructions of the Emergency Manager of the Orderer without delay.
9. Reporting security incidents
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, he is obliged to report it immediately to the utility https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (phone: +420 221 710 911).
